SUMMARIZER="H">

Drought has damaged Illinois River gamefish, killed 3,000 Minnesota turkeys, and 
increased Tennessee livestock sales. Logging at a Michigan forest may be banned.  
Georgia carpet mills may lay off workers. Ohio postponed cloud-seeding for lack of 
clouds. Alabama cotton remains endangered. Indiana and Missouri issued heat alerts. 
Chicago experienced five 100-degree days. Friday's thunderstorms brought Kansas 
tornadoes and Michigan hail. Lightning sparked a Montana forest fire. Railroads, like 
UPS, are offering free transport of hay to Kentucky. Southern hay reached Ohio. 
Minnesota dam flow reductions could affect Fargo's water supply. Wisconsin made $35 
million available for emergency farm loans. National Guardsmen provide an Iowa town's 
drinking water.</SUM>
